[1] Case update
- Wed 18 Sep 2019. CMRE update
[CMRE (Comite Multisectoriel de la Riposte a la maladie a virus Ebola), in French, machine trans., abridged, edited]
https://www.dropbox.com/s/u8i3my874ggn2xx/CMRE_Bulletin%20Ebola%20du%2018%20septembre%202019.pdf?dl=0

Epidemiological situation in the provinces of North Kivu and Ituri on 17 Sep 2019:
Since the beginning of the epidemic, the cumulative number of cases is 3145, of which 3034 are confirmed and 111 probable. In total, there have been 2130 deaths (1992 confirmed and 111 probable) and 961 people recovered.
- 430 suspected cases are under investigation;
- 15 new confirmed cases, including 8 in North Kivu -- 4 in Beni and 4 in Kalunguta; 7 in Ituri, notably 5 in Mandima, 1 in Komanda and 1 in Mandima;
- 5 new confirmed deaths including 1 community death in Oicha in North Kivu; 4 deaths in the Ebola treatment centers (ETCs), notably 1 in Butmebo, 1 in Mabalako, and 1 in Katwa in North Kivu and also 1 in Komanda in Ituri;
- No health worker is among the new confirmed cases. The cumulative number of confirmed/probable cases among health workers is 159 (5% of all confirmed/probable cases), including 41 deaths.

